<HL> Financing Business:
Santa Anita Realty Enterprises Inc.</HL>
<DD> 08/20/87</DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO>
<IN> SAR </IN>
<TEXT>
   SANTA ANITA REALTY ENTERPRISES INC. said it arranged a $50 million line of credit with Union Bank and Wells Fargo &amp; Co. and privately placed $25 million of fixed-rate debt. 
Royce B. McKinley, president of the Los Angeles-based real estate investment trust, which owns the Santa Anita racetack, said the financing program replaces a $20 million line of credit with Union Bank and Security Pacific National Bank. 
The financing will be used in the company's normal real estate investment program, Mr. McKinley said. 

